# .gitignore.example — Developer Growth Mode sharing options

# Default (mirrored in .gitignore): notes and config are gitignored.
# Notes contain a learner's mistakes, prior understanding, and revision history.
# That is private learning material by default.
.claude/growth/notes/
.claude/growth/config.json

# --- OPT-IN: Share the team textbook ---
#
# If your team wants a shared domain-organized textbook that accumulates across
# everyone's sessions, remove the `.claude/growth/notes/` line above and add
# the inversion pattern below to your real .gitignore.
#
# The config.json remains gitignored even in shared mode — level and focus are
# per-developer preferences, not team state.
#
# !.claude/growth/notes/
# !.claude/growth/notes/**
#
# Considerations before opting in:
#   - Notes will contain revision history ("Superseded 2026-05-14: ...") visible to the team.
#   - A junior's foundational notes and a senior's trade-off notes will coexist.
#     That is the point of the layered textbook, but the team should be ready for it.
#   - Notes reveal the team's mistakes over time. Psychological safety matters.
